or" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Denominator">denominator</a> is a <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_of_2" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Power of 2">power of 2</a>. As a result, 1/10 does not have a finite bi=
nary representation (10 has prime factors 2 and 5). This causes 10 =C3=97 1=
/10 not to precisely equal 1 in binary <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Floating-point_arithmetic" title=3D"Floating-point arithmetic">floatin=
g-point arithmetic</a>. As an example, to the binary expansion of 1/3 is .0=
10101..., which means that=20
</p>
