 to Reverend Father Bouvet,<sup>3</sup> the celebrated French Jesuit who li=
ves in Peking, my method of counting by 0 and 1, and nothing more was requi=
red to make him recognize that this was the key to the figures of Fuxi. Wri=
ting to me on 14 November 1701, he sent me this philosophical prince's gran=
d figure, which goes up to 64, and leaves no further room to doubt the trut=
h of our interpretation, such that it can be said that this Father has deci=
phered the enigma of Fuxi, with the help of what I had communicated to him.=
 And as these figures are perhaps the most ancient monument of [GM VII, p22=
